<TITLE> BTRC issues NTTN licence </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 7 (bdnews24.com) - Bangladesh Telecommunication Regulatory Commission has licenced Fibre at Home Ltd to operate a nationwide telecommunication transmission network. "Under the NTTN, the country's telecommunication network will be greatly expanded," says BTRC chairman Maj Gen (retd) Manjurul Alam. "With completion of a coordinated telecommunication network, the rural population will be connected to the telecommunication and internet network." "Increasing rural internet penetration will take the country another step towards a digital Bangladesh," the BTRC chairman said. Under the licence, Fibre at Home Ltd will be responsible for constructing the optical fibre-based telecommunication transmission network, its operation and maintenance, a BTRC press release said on Wednesday. Using the NTTN facilities, the telecommunication service providers can extend the their services to end users. Anyone, except mobile phone and WiMAX operators, can apply for further NTTN licences, BTRC says. bdnews2
